for group, meta in M3Info:
    data, *_ = M3.load(directory='data', group=group)
    unique_elements = data.groupby(['unique_id', 'ds']).size()
    unique_ts = data.groupby('unique_id').size()

    assert (unique_elements != 1).sum() == 0, f'Duplicated records found: {group}'
    assert unique_ts.shape[0] == meta.n_ts, f'Number of time series not match: {group}'

from neuralforecast.data.datasets.m3 import M3, M3Info
from neuralforecast.data.datasets.plots import draw_plot

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import os

if not os.path.exists('./results/'):
    os.makedirs('./results/')

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(20, 30))
ax0 = plt.subplot2grid((4,1),(0, 0))
ax1 = plt.subplot2grid((4,1),(1, 0))
ax2 = plt.subplot2grid((4,1),(2, 0))
ax3 = plt.subplot2grid((4,1),(3, 0))
axs = [ax0, ax1, ax2, ax3]

dataset = M3Info.groups

for idx, group in enumerate(dataset):
    Y_df, _, _ = M3.load(directory='data', group=group)

    x_plot = Y_df[Y_df.unique_id==group[0]+str(1)].ds.values 
    y_plot = Y_df[Y_df.unique_id==group[0]+str(1)].y.values 

    title_str = group
    x_axis_str = f'Period [{str(x_plot.min())[:10]}  to {str(x_plot.max())[:10]}]'
    y_axis_str = group + f' values'

    draw_plot(x_plot, y_plot, title_str, x_axis_str, y_axis_str, axs[idx])

plt.savefig('./results/m3.pdf', bbox_inches = 'tight')
plt.show()
